if a bush fire breaks out without human action, what might have happened? (Australia, 2019-2020)
1. Drought - Severe and prolonged drought can contribute to bush fires. In Australia during the 2019-2020 bushfire season, a prolonged drought led to dry conditions, providing ideal fuel for the fires to ignite and spread.
